"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The predict method of LinearRegression expects a 2D array as input, but np.squeeze(X_te.values) converts it to a 1D array if it has only one column. This will lead to an error. Instead, X_te.values should be passed directly without squeezing it.\", \"patch\": \"15c15\\n< preds = model.predict(np.squeeze(X_te.values))\\n---\\n> preds = model.predict(X_te.values)\"}"